[...]


> I have a quick question. Did the bay window Westfalias
> ever have a front bench seat?

The only bay window Westfalias I have seen with 1/3, 2/3 front seats were
early....before 73. The 2/3 seat hinges in the middle. Does not have a solid
frame like 67 and back.

>If so, was it the same
> vinyl seat that was used in the standard bus models or
> was it ever made with any of the plaid fabric that the
> westfalia bucket seats were made of?

The plaid did not start til 74. Early bays used basket weave. 68 to 72 Westy
used honey vinyl. 73 Westy was gold cloth.

> If their is such
> a thing as a plaid Westy front bench seat, does
> anyone have pictures? Thanks!



